var book = {
	"name": "Daniel",
	"numChapters": 12,
	"chapters": {
		"1": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">1 </span>In the third year of the reign of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21739A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21739A\"></sup>Jehoiakim king of Judah, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21739B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21739B\"></sup>Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon came to Jerusalem and besieged it.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>The <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21740C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21740C\"></sup>Lord gave Jehoiakim king of Judah into his hand, along with some of the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21740D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21740D\"></sup>vessels of the house of God; and he brought them to the land of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21740E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21740E\"></sup>Shinar, to the house of his god, and he brought the vessels into the treasury of his <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21740F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21740F\"></sup>god.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Then the king ordered Ashpenaz, the chief of his officials, to bring in some of the sons of Israel, including some of the royal <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21741G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21741G\"></sup>family and of the nobles,",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>youths in whom was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21742H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21742H\"></sup>no defect, who were good-looking, showing <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21742I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21742I\"></sup>intelligence in every <i>branch of</i> wisdom, endowed with understanding and discerning knowledge, and who had ability for serving in the king’s court; and <i>he ordered him</i> to teach them the literature and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21742J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21742J\"></sup>language of the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21742K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21742K\"></sup>Chaldeans.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>The king appointed for them a daily ration from the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21743L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21743L\"></sup>king’s choice food and from the wine which he drank, and <i>appointed</i> that they should be educated three years, at the end of which they were to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21743M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21743M\"></sup>enter the king’s personal service.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Now among them from the sons of Judah were <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21744N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21744N\"></sup>Daniel, Hananiah, Mishael and Azariah.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Then the commander of the officials assigned <i>new</i> names to them; and to Daniel he assigned <i>the name</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21745O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21745O\"></sup>Belteshazzar, to Hananiah <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21745P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21745P\"></sup>Shadrach, to Mishael <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21745Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21745Q\"></sup>Meshach and to Azariah <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21745R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21745R\"></sup>Abed-nego.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>But Daniel made up his mind that he would not <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21746S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21746S\"></sup>defile himself with the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21746T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21746T\"></sup>king’s choice food or with the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21746U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21746U\"></sup>wine which he drank; so he sought <i>permission</i> from the commander of the officials that he might not defile himself.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Now God granted Daniel <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21747V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21747V\"></sup>favor and compassion in the sight of the commander of the officials,",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>and the commander of the officials said to Daniel, “I am afraid of my lord the king, who has appointed your food and your drink; for why should he see your faces looking more haggard than the youths who are your own age? Then you would make me forfeit my head to the king.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>But Daniel said to the overseer whom the commander of the officials had appointed over Daniel, Hananiah, Mishael and Azariah,",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>“Please test your servants for ten days, and let us be <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21750W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21750W\"></sup>given some vegetables to eat and water to drink.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Then let our appearance be observed in your presence and the appearance of the youths who are eating the king’s choice food; and deal with your servants according to what you see.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>So he listened to them in this matter and tested them for ten days.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>At the end of ten days their appearance seemed <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21753X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21753X\"></sup>better and they were fatter than all the youths who had been eating the king’s choice food.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>So the overseer continued to withhold their choice food and the wine they were to drink, and kept <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21754Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21754Y\"></sup>giving them vegetables.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>As for these four youths, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21755Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21755Z\"></sup>God gave them knowledge and intelligence in every <i>branch of</i> literature and wisdom; Daniel even understood all <i>kinds of</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21755AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21755AA\"></sup>visions and dreams.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Then at the end of the days which the king had specified for presenting them, the commander of the officials presented them before Nebuchadnezzar.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>The king talked with them, and out of them all not one was found like <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21757AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21757AB\"></sup>Daniel, Hananiah, Mishael and Azariah; so they <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21757AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21757AC\"></sup>entered the king’s personal service.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>As for every matter of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21758AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21758AD\"></sup>wisdom and understanding about which the king consulted them, he found them <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21758AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21758AE\"></sup>ten times <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21758AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21758AF\"></sup>better than all the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21758AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21758AG\"></sup>magicians <i>and</i> conjurers who <i>were</i> in all his realm.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>And Daniel continued until the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21759AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21759AH\"></sup>first year of Cyrus the king."
		},
		"2": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">2 </span>Now in the second year of the reign of Nebuchadnezzar, Nebuchadnezzar <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21760A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21760A\"></sup>had dreams; and his spirit was troubled and his <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21760B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21760B\"></sup>sleep left him.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Then the king gave orders to call in the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21761C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21761C\"></sup>magicians, the conjurers, the sorcerers and the Chaldeans to tell the king his dreams. So they came in and stood before the king.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>The king said to them, “I <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21762D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21762D\"></sup>had a dream and my spirit is anxious to understand the dream.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Then the Chaldeans spoke to the king in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21763E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21763E\"></sup>Aramaic: “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21763F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21763F\"></sup>O king, live forever! <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21763G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21763G\"></sup>Tell the dream to your servants, and we will declare the interpretation.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>The king replied to the Chaldeans, “The command from me is firm: if you do not make known to me the dream and its interpretation, you will be <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21764H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21764H\"></sup>torn limb from limb and your houses will be made a rubbish heap.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>But if you declare the dream and its interpretation, you will receive from me <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21765I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21765I\"></sup>gifts and a reward and great honor; therefore declare to me the dream and its interpretation.”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>They answered a second time and said, “Let the king <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21766J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21766J\"></sup>tell the dream to his servants, and we will declare the interpretation.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>The king replied, “I know for certain that you are bargaining for time, inasmuch as you have seen that the command from me is firm,",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>that if you do not make the dream known to me, there is only <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21768K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21768K\"></sup>one decree for you. For you have agreed together to speak lying and corrupt words before me until the situation is changed; therefore tell me the dream, that I may <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21768L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21768L\"></sup>know that you can declare to me its interpretation.”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>The Chaldeans answered the king and said, “There is not a man on earth who could declare the matter for the king, inasmuch as no great king or ruler has <i>ever</i> asked anything like this of any <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21769M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21769M\"></sup>magician, conjurer or Chaldean.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Moreover, the thing which the king demands is difficult, and there is no one else who could declare it to the king except <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21770N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21770N\"></sup>gods, whose <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21770O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21770O\"></sup>dwelling place is not with <i>mortal</i> flesh.”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Because of this the king became <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21771P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21771P\"></sup>indignant and very furious and gave orders to destroy all the wise men of Babylon.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>So the decree went forth that the wise men should be slain; and they looked for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21772Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21772Q\"></sup>Daniel and his friends to kill <i>them</i>.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Then Daniel replied with discretion and discernment to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21773R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21773R\"></sup>Arioch, the captain of the king’s bodyguard, who had gone forth to slay the wise men of Babylon;",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>he said to Arioch, the king’s commander, “For what reason is the decree from the king <i>so</i> urgent?” Then Arioch informed Daniel about the matter.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>So Daniel went in and requested of the king that he would give him time, in order that he might declare the interpretation to the king.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Then Daniel went to his house and informed his friends, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21776S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21776S\"></sup>Hananiah, Mishael and Azariah, about the matter,",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>so that they might <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21777T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21777T\"></sup>request compassion from the God of heaven concerning this mystery, so that Daniel and his friends would not be <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21777U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21777U\"></sup>destroyed with the rest of the wise men of Babylon.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Then the mystery was revealed to Daniel in a night <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21778V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21778V\"></sup>vision. Then Daniel blessed the God of heaven;",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Daniel said,“Let the name of God be <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21779W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21779W\"></sup>blessed forever and ever,For <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21779X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21779X\"></sup>wisdom and power belong to Him.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>“It is He who <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21780Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21780Y\"></sup>changes the times and the epochs;He <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21780Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21780Z\"></sup>removes kings and establishes kings;He gives <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21780AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21780AA\"></sup>wisdom to wise menAnd knowledge to men of understanding.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>“It is He who <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21781AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21781AB\"></sup>reveals the profound and hidden things;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21781AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21781AC\"></sup>He knows what is in the darkness,And the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21781AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21781AD\"></sup>light dwells with Him.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>“To You, O <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21782AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21782AE\"></sup>God of my fathers, I give thanks and praise,For You have given me <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21782AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21782AF\"></sup>wisdom and power;Even now You have made known to me what we <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21782AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21782AG\"></sup>requested of You,For You have made known to us the king’s matter.”",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Therefore, Daniel went in to Arioch, whom the king had appointed to destroy the wise men of Babylon; he went and spoke to him as follows: “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21783AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21783AH\"></sup>Do not destroy the wise men of Babylon! Take me into the king’s presence, and I will declare the interpretation to the king.”",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Then Arioch hurriedly <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21784AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21784AI\"></sup>brought Daniel into the king’s presence and spoke to him as follows: “I have found a man among the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21784AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21784AJ\"></sup>exiles from Judah who can make the interpretation known to the king!”",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>The king said to Daniel, whose name was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21785AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21785AK\"></sup>Belteshazzar, “Are you able to make known to me the dream which I have seen and its interpretation?”",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Daniel answered before the king and said, “As for the mystery about which the king has inquired, neither <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21786AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21786AL\"></sup>wise men, conjurers, magicians <i>nor</i> diviners are able to declare <i>it</i> to the king.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>However, there is a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21787AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21787AM\"></sup>God in heaven who reveals mysteries, and He has made known to King Nebuchadnezzar what will take place in the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21787AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21787AN\"></sup>latter days. This was your dream and the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21787AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21787AO\"></sup>visions in your mind <i>while</i> on your bed.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>As for you, O king, <i>while</i> on your bed your thoughts turned to what would take place in the future; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21788AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21788AP\"></sup>He who reveals mysteries has made known to you what will take place.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>But as for me, this mystery has not been revealed to me for any <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21789AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21789AQ\"></sup>wisdom residing in me more than <i>in</i> any <i>other</i> living man, but for the purpose of making the interpretation known to the king, and that you may understand the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21789AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21789AR\"></sup>thoughts of your mind.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>“You, O king, were looking and behold, there was a single great statue; that statue, which was large and of extraordinary splendor, was standing in front of you, and its appearance was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21790AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21790AS\"></sup>awesome.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>The <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21791AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21791AT\"></sup>head of that statue <i>was made</i> of fine gold, its breast and its arms of silver, its belly and its thighs of bronze,",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>its legs of iron, its feet partly of iron and partly of clay.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>You continued looking until a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21793AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21793AU\"></sup>stone was cut out <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21793AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21793AV\"></sup>without hands, and it struck the statue on its feet of iron and clay and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21793AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21793AW\"></sup>crushed them.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>Then the iron, the clay, the bronze, the silver and the gold were crushed all at the same time and became <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21794AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21794AX\"></sup>like chaff from the summer threshing floors; and the wind carried them away so that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21794AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21794AY\"></sup>not a trace of them was found. But the stone that struck the statue became a great <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21794AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21794AZ\"></sup>mountain and filled the whole earth.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>“This <i>was</i> the dream; now we will tell <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21795BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21795BA\"></sup>its interpretation before the king.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>You, O king, are the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21796BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21796BB\"></sup>king of kings, to whom the God of heaven has given the kingdom, the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21796BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21796BC\"></sup>power, the strength and the glory;",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>and wherever the sons of men dwell, <i>or</i> the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21797BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21797BD\"></sup>beasts of the field, or the birds of the sky, He has given <i>them</i> into your hand and has caused you to rule over them all. You are the head of gold.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>After you there will arise another kingdom inferior to you, then another third kingdom of bronze, which will rule over all the earth.",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>Then there will be a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21799BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21799BE\"></sup>fourth kingdom as strong as iron; inasmuch as iron crushes and shatters all things, so, like iron that breaks in pieces, it will crush and break all these in pieces.",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>In that you saw the feet and toes, partly of potter’s clay and partly of iron, it will be a divided kingdom; but it will have in it the toughness of iron, inasmuch as you saw the iron mixed with common clay.",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup><i>As</i> the toes of the feet <i>were</i> partly of iron and partly of pottery, <i>so</i> some of the kingdom will be strong and part of it will be brittle.",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>And in that you saw the iron mixed with common clay, they will combine with one another in the seed of men; but they will not adhere to one another, even as iron does not combine with pottery.",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>In the days of those kings the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21803BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21803BF\"></sup>God of heaven will <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21803BG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BG&quot;&gt;BG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21803BG\"></sup>set up a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21803BH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BH&quot;&gt;BH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21803BH\"></sup>kingdom which will never be destroyed, and <i>that</i> kingdom will not be left for another people; it will <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21803BI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BI&quot;&gt;BI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21803BI\"></sup>crush and put an end to all these kingdoms, but it will itself endure forever.",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>Inasmuch as you saw that a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21804BJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BJ&quot;&gt;BJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21804BJ\"></sup>stone was cut out of the mountain without hands and that it crushed the iron, the bronze, the clay, the silver and the gold, the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21804BK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BK&quot;&gt;BK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21804BK\"></sup>great God has made known to the king what <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21804BL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BL&quot;&gt;BL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21804BL\"></sup>will take place in the future; so the dream is true and its interpretation is trustworthy.”",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>Then King Nebuchadnezzar fell on his face and did <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21805BM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BM&quot;&gt;BM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21805BM\"></sup>homage to Daniel, and gave orders to present to him an offering and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21805BN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BN&quot;&gt;BN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21805BN\"></sup>fragrant incense.",
			"47": "<sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup>The king answered Daniel and said, “Surely <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21806BO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BO&quot;&gt;BO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21806BO\"></sup>your God is a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21806BP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BP&quot;&gt;BP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21806BP\"></sup>God of gods and a Lord of kings and a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21806BQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BQ&quot;&gt;BQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21806BQ\"></sup>revealer of mysteries, since you have been able to reveal this mystery.”",
			"48": "<sup class=\"versenum\">48 </sup>Then the king <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21807BR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BR&quot;&gt;BR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21807BR\"></sup>promoted Daniel and gave him many great gifts, and he made him ruler over the whole <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21807BS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BS&quot;&gt;BS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21807BS\"></sup>province of Babylon and chief prefect over all the wise men of Babylon.",
			"49": "<sup class=\"versenum\">49 </sup>And Daniel made request of the king, and he <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21808BT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BT&quot;&gt;BT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21808BT\"></sup>appointed <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21808BU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BU&quot;&gt;BU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21808BU\"></sup>Shadrach, Meshach and Abed-nego over the administration of the province of Babylon, while Daniel <i>was</i> at the king’s <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21808BV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BV&quot;&gt;BV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21808BV\"></sup>court."
		},
		"3": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">3 </span>Nebuchadnezzar the king made an <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21809A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21809A\"></sup>image of gold, the height of which <i>was</i> sixty cubits <i>and</i> its width six cubits; he set it up on the plain of Dura in the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21809B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21809B\"></sup>province of Babylon.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Then Nebuchadnezzar the king sent <i>word</i> to assemble the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21810C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21810C\"></sup>satraps, the prefects and the governors, the counselors, the treasurers, the judges, the magistrates and all the rulers of the provinces to come to the dedication of the image that Nebuchadnezzar the king had set up.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Then the satraps, the prefects and the governors, the counselors, the treasurers, the judges, the magistrates and all the rulers of the provinces were assembled for the dedication of the image that Nebuchadnezzar the king had set up; and they stood before the image that Nebuchadnezzar had set up.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Then the herald loudly proclaimed: “To you the command is given, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21812D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21812D\"></sup>O peoples, nations and <i>men of every</i> language,",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>that at the moment you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21813E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21813E\"></sup>hear the sound of the horn, flute, lyre, trigon, psaltery, bagpipe and all kinds of music, you are to fall down and worship the golden image that Nebuchadnezzar the king has set up.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>But whoever does not fall down and worship shall immediately be <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21814F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21814F\"></sup>cast into the midst of a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21814G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21814G\"></sup>furnace of blazing fire.”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Therefore at that time, when all the peoples heard the sound of the horn, flute, lyre, trigon, psaltery, bagpipe and all kinds of music, all the peoples, nations and <i>men of every</i> language fell down <i>and</i> worshiped the golden image that Nebuchadnezzar the king had set up.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>For this reason at that time certain <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21816H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21816H\"></sup>Chaldeans came forward and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21816I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21816I\"></sup>brought charges against the Jews.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>They responded and said to Nebuchadnezzar the king: “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21817J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21817J\"></sup>O king, live forever!",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>You, O king, have <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21818K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21818K\"></sup>made a decree that every man who hears the sound of the horn, flute, lyre, trigon, psaltery, and bagpipe and all kinds of music, is to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21818L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21818L\"></sup>fall down and worship the golden image.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>But whoever does not fall down and worship shall be cast into the midst of a furnace of blazing fire.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>There are certain Jews whom you have <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21820M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21820M\"></sup>appointed over the administration of the province of Babylon, <i>namely</i> Shadrach, Meshach and Abed-nego. These men, O king, have disregarded you; they do not serve your gods or worship the golden image which you have set up.”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Then Nebuchadnezzar in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21821N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21821N\"></sup>rage and anger gave orders to bring Shadrach, Meshach and Abed-nego; then these men were brought before the king.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Nebuchadnezzar responded and said to them, “Is it true, Shadrach, Meshach and Abed-nego, that you do not serve <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21822O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21822O\"></sup>my gods or worship the golden image that I have set up?",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Now if you are ready, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21823P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21823P\"></sup>at the moment you hear the sound of the horn, flute, lyre, trigon, psaltery and bagpipe and all kinds of music, to fall down and worship the image that I have made, <i>very well</i>. But if you do not worship, you will immediately be <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21823Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21823Q\"></sup>cast into the midst of a furnace of blazing fire; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21823R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21823R\"></sup>what god is there who can deliver you out of my hands?”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21824S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21824S\"></sup>Shadrach, Meshach and Abed-nego replied to the king, “O Nebuchadnezzar, we do not need to give you an answer concerning this matter.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>If it be <i>so</i>, our <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21825T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21825T\"></sup>God whom we serve is able to deliver us from the furnace of blazing fire; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21825U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21825U\"></sup>He will deliver us out of your hand, O king.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21826V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21826V\"></sup>But <i>even</i> if <i>He does</i> not, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21826W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21826W\"></sup>let it be known to you, O king, that we are not going to serve your gods or worship the golden image that you have set up.”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Then Nebuchadnezzar was filled with <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21827X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21827X\"></sup>wrath, and his facial expression was altered toward Shadrach, Meshach and Abed-nego. He answered by giving orders to heat the furnace seven times more than it was usually heated.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>He commanded certain valiant warriors who <i>were</i> in his army to tie up Shadrach, Meshach and Abed-nego in order to cast <i>them</i> into the furnace of blazing fire.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Then these men were tied up in their <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21829Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21829Y\"></sup>trousers, their coats, their caps and their <i>other</i> clothes, and were cast into the midst of the furnace of blazing fire.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>For this reason, because the king’s command <i>was</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21830Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21830Z\"></sup>urgent and the furnace had been made extremely hot, the flame of the fire slew those men who carried up Shadrach, Meshach and Abed-nego.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>But these three men, Shadrach, Meshach and Abed-nego, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21831AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21831AA\"></sup>fell into the midst of the furnace of blazing fire <i>still</i> tied up.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Then Nebuchadnezzar the king was astounded and stood up in haste; he said to his high officials, “Was it not three men we cast bound into the midst of the fire?” They replied to the king, “Certainly, O king.”",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>He said, “Look! I see four men loosed <i>and</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21833AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21833AB\"></sup>walking <i>about</i> in the midst of the fire without harm, and the appearance of the fourth is like a son of <i>the</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21833AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21833AC\"></sup>gods!”",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Then Nebuchadnezzar came near to the door of the furnace of blazing fire; he responded and said, “Shadrach, Meshach and Abed-nego, come out, you servants of the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21834AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21834AD\"></sup>Most High God, and come here!” Then Shadrach, Meshach and Abed-nego <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21834AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21834AE\"></sup>came out of the midst of the fire.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>The <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21835AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21835AF\"></sup>satraps, the prefects, the governors and the king’s high officials gathered around <i>and</i> saw in regard to these men that the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21835AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21835AG\"></sup>fire had no effect on the bodies of these men nor was the hair of their head singed, nor were their <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21835AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21835AH\"></sup>trousers damaged, nor had the smell of fire <i>even</i> come upon them.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Nebuchadnezzar responded and said, “Blessed be the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21836AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21836AI\"></sup>God of Shadrach, Meshach and Abed-nego, who has <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21836AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21836AJ\"></sup>sent His angel and delivered His servants who put their <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21836AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21836AK\"></sup>trust in Him, violating the king’s command, and yielded up their bodies so as <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21836AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21836AL\"></sup>not to serve or worship any god except their own God.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Therefore I <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21837AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21837AM\"></sup>make a decree that any people, nation or tongue that speaks anything offensive against the God of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21837AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21837AN\"></sup>Shadrach, Meshach and Abed-nego shall be torn limb from limb and their <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21837AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21837AO\"></sup>houses reduced to a rubbish heap, inasmuch as there is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21837AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21837AP\"></sup>no other god who is able to deliver in this way.”",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Then the king <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21838AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21838AQ\"></sup>caused Shadrach, Meshach and Abed-nego to prosper in the province of Babylon."
		},
		"4": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">4 </span>Nebuchadnezzar the king to all the peoples, nations, and <i>men of every</i> language that live in all the earth: “May your <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21839A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21839A\"></sup>peace abound!",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>It has seemed good to me to declare the signs and wonders which the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21840B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21840B\"></sup>Most High God has done for me.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>“How great are His <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21841C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21841C\"></sup>signsAnd how mighty are His wonders!His <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21841D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21841D\"></sup>kingdom is an everlasting kingdomAnd His dominion is from generation to generation.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>“I, Nebuchadnezzar, was at ease in my house and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21842E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21842E\"></sup>flourishing in my palace.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>I saw a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21843F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21843F\"></sup>dream and it made me fearful; and <i>these</i> fantasies <i>as I lay</i> on my bed and the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21843G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21843G\"></sup>visions in my mind kept alarming me.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>So I gave orders to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21844H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21844H\"></sup>bring into my presence all the wise men of Babylon, that they might make known to me the interpretation of the dream.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Then the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21845I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21845I\"></sup>magicians, the conjurers, the Chaldeans and the diviners came in and I related the dream to them, but they could not make its <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21845J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21845J\"></sup>interpretation known to me.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>But finally Daniel came in before me, whose name is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21846K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21846K\"></sup>Belteshazzar according to the name of my god, and in whom is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21846L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21846L\"></sup>a spirit of the holy gods; and I related the dream to him, <i>saying</i>,",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>‘O Belteshazzar, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21847M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21847M\"></sup>chief of the magicians, since I know that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21847N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21847N\"></sup>a spirit of the holy gods is in you and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21847O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21847O\"></sup>no mystery baffles you, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21847P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21847P\"></sup>tell <i>me</i> the visions of my dream which I have seen, along with its interpretation.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>‘Now <i>these were</i> the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21848Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21848Q\"></sup>visions in my mind <i>as I lay</i> on my bed: I was looking, and behold, <i>there was</i> a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21848R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21848R\"></sup>tree in the midst of the earth and its height <i>was</i> great.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>‘The tree grew large and became strongAnd its height <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21849S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21849S\"></sup>reached to the sky,And it <i>was</i> visible to the end of the whole earth.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>‘Its foliage <i>was</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21850T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21850T\"></sup>beautiful and its fruit abundant,And in it <i>was</i> food for all.The <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21850U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21850U\"></sup>beasts of the field found <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21850V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21850V\"></sup>shade under it,And the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21850W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21850W\"></sup>birds of the sky dwelt in its branches,And all living creatures fed themselves from it.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>‘I was looking in the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21851X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21851X\"></sup>visions in my mind <i>as I lay</i> on my bed, and behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21851Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21851Y\"></sup>an <i>angelic</i> watcher, a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21851Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21851Z\"></sup>holy one, descended from heaven.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>‘He shouted out and spoke as follows:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21852AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21852AA\"></sup>Chop down the tree and cut off its branches,Strip off its foliage and scatter its fruit;Let the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21852AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21852AB\"></sup>beasts flee from under itAnd the birds from its branches.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>“Yet <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21853AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21853AC\"></sup>leave the stump with its roots in the ground,But with a band of iron and bronze <i>around it</i>In the new grass of the field;And let him be drenched with the dew of heaven,And let him share with the beasts in the grass of the earth.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>“Let his mind be changed from <i>that of</i> a manAnd let a beast’s mind be given to him,And let <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21854AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21854AD\"></sup>seven periods of time pass over him.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>“This sentence is by the decree of the <i>angelic</i> watchersAnd the decision is a command of the holy ones,In order that the living may <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21855AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21855AE\"></sup>knowThat the Most High is ruler over the realm of mankind,And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21855AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21855AF\"></sup>bestows it on whom He wishesAnd sets over it the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21855AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21855AG\"></sup>lowliest of men.”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>This is the dream <i>which</i> I, King Nebuchadnezzar, have seen. Now you, Belteshazzar, tell <i>me</i> its interpretation, inasmuch as none of the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21856AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21856AH\"></sup>wise men of my kingdom is able to make known to me the interpretation; but you are able, for a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21856AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21856AI\"></sup>spirit of the holy gods is in you.’",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>“Then Daniel, whose name is Belteshazzar, was appalled for a while as his <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21857AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21857AJ\"></sup>thoughts alarmed him. The king responded and said, ‘Belteshazzar, do not <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21857AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21857AK\"></sup>let the dream or its interpretation alarm you.’ Belteshazzar replied, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21857AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21857AL\"></sup>My lord, <i>if only</i> the dream applied to those who hate you and its interpretation to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21857AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21857AM\"></sup>your adversaries!",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>The <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21858AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21858AN\"></sup>tree that you saw, which became large and grew strong, whose height reached to the sky and was visible to all the earth",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>and whose foliage <i>was</i> beautiful and its fruit abundant, and in which <i>was</i> food for all, under which the beasts of the field dwelt and in whose branches the birds of the sky lodged—",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>it is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21860AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21860AO\"></sup>you, O king; for you have become great and grown strong, and your majesty has become great and reached to the sky and your <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21860AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21860AP\"></sup>dominion to the end of the earth.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>In that the king saw an <i>angelic</i> watcher, a holy one, descending from heaven and saying, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21861AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21861AQ\"></sup>Chop down the tree and destroy it; yet leave the stump with its roots in the ground, but with a band of iron and bronze <i>around it</i> in the new grass of the field, and let him be drenched with the dew of heaven, and let him share with the beasts of the field until <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21861AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21861AR\"></sup>seven periods of time pass over him,”",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>this is the interpretation, O king, and this is the decree of the Most High, which has <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21862AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21862AS\"></sup>come upon my lord the king:",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>that you be <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21863AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21863AT\"></sup>driven away from mankind and your dwelling place be with the beasts of the field, and you be given grass to eat like cattle and be drenched with the dew of heaven; and seven periods of time will pass over you, until you recognize that the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21863AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21863AU\"></sup>Most High is ruler over the realm of mankind and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21863AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21863AV\"></sup>bestows it on whomever He wishes.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>And in that it was commanded to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21864AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21864AW\"></sup>leave the stump with the roots of the tree, your kingdom will be assured to you after you recognize that <i>it is</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21864AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21864AX\"></sup>Heaven <i>that</i> rules.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Therefore, O king, may my <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21865AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21865AY\"></sup>advice be pleasing to you: <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21865AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21865AZ\"></sup>break away now from your sins by <i>doing</i> righteousness and from your iniquities by <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21865BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21865BA\"></sup>showing mercy to <i>the</i> poor, in case there may be a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21865BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21865BB\"></sup>prolonging of your prosperity.’",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>“All <i>this</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21866BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21866BC\"></sup>happened to Nebuchadnezzar the king.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21867BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21867BD\"></sup>Twelve months later he was walking on the <i>roof of</i> the royal palace of Babylon.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>The king reflected and said, ‘Is this not Babylon the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21868BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21868BE\"></sup>great, which I myself have built as a royal residence by the might of my power and for the glory of my majesty?’",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>While the word <i>was</i> in the king’s mouth, a voice came from heaven, <i>saying</i>, ‘King Nebuchadnezzar, to you it is declared: sovereignty has been removed from you,",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21870BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21870BF\"></sup>you will be driven away from mankind, and your dwelling place <i>will be</i> with the beasts of the field. You will be given grass to eat like cattle, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21870BG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BG&quot;&gt;BG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21870BG\"></sup>seven periods of time will pass over you until you recognize that the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21870BH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BH&quot;&gt;BH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21870BH\"></sup>Most High is ruler over the realm of mankind and bestows it on whomever He wishes.’",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>Immediately the word concerning Nebuchadnezzar was fulfilled; and he was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21871BI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BI&quot;&gt;BI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21871BI\"></sup>driven away from mankind and began eating grass like cattle, and his body was drenched with the dew of heaven until his hair had grown like eagles’ <i>feathers</i> and his nails like birds’ <i>claws</i>.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>“But at the end of that period, I, Nebuchadnezzar, raised my eyes toward heaven and my reason returned to me, and I blessed the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21872BJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BJ&quot;&gt;BJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21872BJ\"></sup>Most High and praised and honored <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21872BK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BK&quot;&gt;BK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21872BK\"></sup>Him who lives forever;For His dominion is an <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21872BL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BL&quot;&gt;BL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21872BL\"></sup>everlasting dominion,And His kingdom <i>endures</i> from generation to generation.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21873BM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BM&quot;&gt;BM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21873BM\"></sup>All the inhabitants of the earth are accounted as nothing,But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21873BN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BN&quot;&gt;BN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21873BN\"></sup>He does according to His will in the host of heavenAnd <i>among</i> the inhabitants of earth;And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21873BO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BO&quot;&gt;BO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21873BO\"></sup>no one can ward off His handOr say to Him, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21873BP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BP&quot;&gt;BP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21873BP\"></sup>What have You done?’",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>At that time my <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21874BQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BQ&quot;&gt;BQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21874BQ\"></sup>reason returned to me. And my majesty and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21874BR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BR&quot;&gt;BR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21874BR\"></sup>splendor were restored to me for the glory of my kingdom, and my counselors and my nobles began seeking me out; so I was reestablished in my sovereignty, and surpassing <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21874BS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BS&quot;&gt;BS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21874BS\"></sup>greatness was added to me.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>Now I, Nebuchadnezzar, praise, exalt and honor the King of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21875BT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BT&quot;&gt;BT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21875BT\"></sup>heaven, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21875BU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BU&quot;&gt;BU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21875BU\"></sup>all His works are true and His ways just, and He is able to humble those who <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21875BV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BV&quot;&gt;BV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21875BV\"></sup>walk in pride.”"
		},
		"5": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">5 </span>Belshazzar the king held a great <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21876A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21876A\"></sup>feast for a thousand of his nobles, and he was drinking wine in the presence of the thousand.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>When Belshazzar tasted the wine, he gave orders to bring the gold and silver <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21877B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21877B\"></sup>vessels which Nebuchadnezzar his father had taken out of the temple which <i>was</i> in Jerusalem, so that the king and his nobles, his wives and his concubines might drink from them.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Then they brought the gold vessels that had been taken out of the temple, the house of God which <i>was</i> in Jerusalem; and the king and his nobles, his wives and his concubines drank from them.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>They <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21879C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21879C\"></sup>drank the wine and praised the gods of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21879D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21879D\"></sup>gold and silver, of bronze, iron, wood and stone.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Suddenly the fingers of a man’s hand emerged and began writing opposite the lampstand on the plaster of the wall of the king’s palace, and the king saw the back of the hand that did the writing.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Then the king’s <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21881E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21881E\"></sup>face grew pale and his thoughts alarmed him, and his <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21881F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21881F\"></sup>hip joints went slack and his <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21881G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21881G\"></sup>knees began knocking together.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>The king called aloud to bring in the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21882H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21882H\"></sup>conjurers, the Chaldeans and the diviners. The king spoke and said to the wise men of Babylon, “Any man who can read this inscription and explain its interpretation to me shall be <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21882I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21882I\"></sup>clothed with purple and <i>have</i> a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21882J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21882J\"></sup>necklace of gold around his neck, and have authority as <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21882K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21882K\"></sup>third <i>ruler</i> in the kingdom.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Then all the king’s wise men came in, but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21883L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21883L\"></sup>they could not read the inscription or make known its interpretation to the king.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Then King Belshazzar was greatly <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21884M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21884M\"></sup>alarmed, his <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21884N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21884N\"></sup>face grew <i>even</i> paler, and his nobles were perplexed.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>The queen entered the banquet hall because of the words of the king and his nobles; the queen spoke and said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21885O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21885O\"></sup>O king, live forever! Do not let your thoughts alarm you or your face be pale.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>There is a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21886P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21886P\"></sup>man in your kingdom in whom is a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21886Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21886Q\"></sup>spirit of the holy gods; and in the days of your father, illumination, insight and wisdom like the wisdom of the gods were found in him. And King Nebuchadnezzar, your father, your father <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21886R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21886R\"></sup>the king, appointed him chief of the magicians, conjurers, Chaldeans <i>and</i> diviners.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup><i>This was</i> because an <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21887S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21887S\"></sup>extraordinary spirit, knowledge and insight, interpretation of dreams, explanation of enigmas and solving of difficult problems were found in this Daniel, whom the king named <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21887T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21887T\"></sup>Belteshazzar. Let Daniel now be summoned and he will declare the interpretation.”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Then Daniel was brought in before the king. The king spoke and said to Daniel, “Are you that Daniel who is one of the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21888U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21888U\"></sup>exiles from Judah, whom my father the king <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21888V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21888V\"></sup>brought from Judah?",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Now I have heard about you that a spirit of the gods is in you, and that illumination, insight and extraordinary wisdom have been found in you.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Just now the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21890W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21890W\"></sup>wise men <i>and</i> the conjurers were brought in before me that they might read this inscription and make its interpretation known to me, but they <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21890X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21890X\"></sup>could not declare the interpretation of the message.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>But I personally have heard about you, that you are able to give interpretations and solve difficult problems. Now if you are able to read the inscription and make its <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21891Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21891Y\"></sup>interpretation known to me, you will be <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21891Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21891Z\"></sup>clothed with purple and <i>wear</i> a necklace of gold around your neck, and you will have authority as the third <i>ruler</i> in the kingdom.”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Then Daniel answered and said before the king, “Keep your <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21892AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21892AA\"></sup>gifts for yourself or give your rewards to someone else; however, I will read the inscription to the king and make the interpretation known to him.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>O king, the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21893AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21893AB\"></sup>Most High God <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21893AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21893AC\"></sup>granted sovereignty, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21893AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21893AD\"></sup>grandeur, glory and majesty to Nebuchadnezzar your father.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Because of the grandeur which He bestowed on him, all the peoples, nations and <i>men of every</i> language feared and trembled before him; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21894AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21894AE\"></sup>whomever he wished he killed and whomever he wished he spared alive; and whomever he wished he elevated and whomever he wished he humbled.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>But when his heart was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21895AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21895AF\"></sup>lifted up and his spirit became so <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21895AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21895AG\"></sup>proud that he behaved arrogantly, he was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21895AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21895AH\"></sup>deposed from his royal throne and <i>his</i> glory was taken away from him.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>He was also <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21896AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21896AI\"></sup>driven away from mankind, and his heart was made like <i>that of</i> beasts, and his dwelling place <i>was</i> with the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21896AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21896AJ\"></sup>wild donkeys. He was given grass to eat like cattle, and his body was drenched with the dew of heaven until he recognized that the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21896AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21896AK\"></sup>Most High God is ruler over the realm of mankind and <i>that</i> He sets over it whomever He wishes.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Yet you, his son, Belshazzar, have <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21897AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21897AL\"></sup>not humbled your heart, even though you knew all this,",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>but you have <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21898AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21898AM\"></sup>exalted yourself against the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21898AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21898AN\"></sup>Lord of heaven; and they have brought the vessels of His house before you, and you and your nobles, your wives and your concubines have been drinking wine from them; and you have praised the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21898AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21898AO\"></sup>gods of silver and gold, of bronze, iron, wood and stone, which do not see, hear or understand. But the God <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21898AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21898AP\"></sup>in whose hand are your life-breath and all your <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21898AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21898AQ\"></sup>ways, you have not glorified.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Then the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21899AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21899AR\"></sup>hand was sent from Him and this inscription was written out.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>“Now this is the inscription that was written out: ‘MENĒ, MENĒ, TEKĒL, UPHARSIN.’",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>This is the interpretation of the message: ‘MENĒ’—God has numbered your kingdom and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21901AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21901AS\"></sup>put an end to it.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>‘TEKĒL’—you have been <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21902AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21902AT\"></sup>weighed on the scales and found deficient.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>‘PERĒS’—your kingdom has been divided and given over to the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21903AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21903AU\"></sup>Medes and Persians.”",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Then Belshazzar gave orders, and they <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21904AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21904AV\"></sup>clothed Daniel with purple and <i>put</i> a necklace of gold around his neck, and issued a proclamation concerning him that he <i>now</i> had authority as the third <i>ruler</i> in the kingdom.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>That same night <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21905AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21905AW\"></sup>Belshazzar the Chaldean king was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21905AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21905AX\"></sup>slain.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>So <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21906AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21906AY\"></sup>Darius the Mede received the kingdom at about the age of sixty-two."
		},
		"6": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">6 </span>It seemed good to Darius to appoint 120 satraps over the kingdom, that they would be in charge of the whole kingdom,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>and over them three commissioners (of whom <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21908A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21908A\"></sup>Daniel was one), that these satraps might be accountable to them, and that the king might not suffer <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21908B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21908B\"></sup>loss.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Then this Daniel began distinguishing himself among the commissioners and satraps because he possessed an <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21909C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21909C\"></sup>extraordinary spirit, and the king planned to appoint him over the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21909D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21909D\"></sup>entire kingdom.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Then the commissioners and satraps began <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21910E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21910E\"></sup>trying to find a ground of accusation against Daniel in regard to government affairs; but they could find <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21910F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21910F\"></sup>no ground of accusation or <i>evidence of</i> corruption, inasmuch as he was faithful, and no negligence or corruption was <i>to be</i> found in him.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Then these men said, “We will not find any ground of accusation against this Daniel unless we find <i>it</i> against him with regard to the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21911G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21911G\"></sup>law of his God.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Then these commissioners and satraps came by agreement to the king and spoke to him as follows: “King Darius, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21912H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21912H\"></sup>live forever!",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>All the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21913I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21913I\"></sup>commissioners of the kingdom, the prefects and the satraps, the high officials and the governors have <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21913J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21913J\"></sup>consulted together that the king should establish a statute and enforce an injunction that anyone who makes a petition to any god or man besides you, O king, for thirty days, shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21913K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21913K\"></sup>be cast into the lions’ den.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Now, O king, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21914L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21914L\"></sup>establish the injunction and sign the document so that it may not be changed, according to the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21914M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21914M\"></sup>law of the Medes and Persians, which may not be revoked.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Therefore King Darius <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21915N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21915N\"></sup>signed the document, that is, the injunction.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Now when Daniel knew that the document was signed, he entered his house (now in his roof chamber he had windows open <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21916O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21916O\"></sup>toward Jerusalem); and he continued <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21916P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21916P\"></sup>kneeling on his knees three times a day, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21916Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21916Q\"></sup>praying and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21916R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21916R\"></sup>giving thanks before his God, as he had been doing previously.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Then these men came <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21917S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21917S\"></sup>by agreement and found Daniel making petition and supplication before his God.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Then they approached and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21918T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21918T\"></sup>spoke before the king about the king’s injunction, “Did you not sign an injunction that any man who makes a petition to any god or man besides you, O king, for thirty days, is to be cast into the lions’ den?” The king replied, “The statement is true, according to the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21918U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21918U\"></sup>law of the Medes and Persians, which may not be revoked.”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Then they answered and spoke before the king, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21919V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21919V\"></sup>Daniel, who is one of the exiles from Judah, pays <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21919W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21919W\"></sup>no attention to you, O king, or to the injunction which you signed, but keeps making his petition three times a day.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Then, as soon as the king heard this statement, he was deeply <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21920X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21920X\"></sup>distressed and set <i>his</i> mind on delivering Daniel; and even until sunset he kept exerting himself to rescue him.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Then these men came by agreement to the king and said to the king, “Recognize, O king, that it is a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21921Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21921Y\"></sup>law of the Medes and Persians that no injunction or statute which the king establishes may be changed.”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Then the king gave orders, and Daniel was brought in and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21922Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21922Z\"></sup>cast into the lions’ den. The king spoke and said to Daniel, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21922AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21922AA\"></sup>Your God whom you constantly serve will Himself deliver you.”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>A <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21923AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21923AB\"></sup>stone was brought and laid over the mouth of the den; and the king sealed it with his own signet ring and with the signet rings of his nobles, so that nothing would be changed in regard to Daniel.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Then the king went off to his palace and spent the night <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21924AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21924AC\"></sup>fasting, and no entertainment was brought before him; and his <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21924AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21924AD\"></sup>sleep fled from him.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Then the king arose at dawn, at the break of day, and went in haste to the lions’ den.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>When he had come near the den to Daniel, he cried out with a troubled voice. The king spoke and said to Daniel, “Daniel, servant of the living God, has <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21926AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21926AE\"></sup>your God, whom you constantly serve, been <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21926AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21926AF\"></sup>able to deliver you from the lions?”",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Then Daniel spoke to the king, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21927AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21927AG\"></sup>O king, live forever!",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>My God <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21928AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21928AH\"></sup>sent His angel and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21928AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21928AI\"></sup>shut the lions’ mouths and they have not harmed me, inasmuch as I was found innocent before Him; and also toward you, O king, I have committed no crime.”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Then the king was very pleased and gave orders for Daniel to be taken up out of the den. So Daniel was taken up out of the den and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21929AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21929AJ\"></sup>no injury whatever was found on him, because he had <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21929AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21929AK\"></sup>trusted in his God.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>The king then gave orders, and they brought those men who had maliciously accused Daniel, and they <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21930AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21930AL\"></sup>cast them, their <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21930AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21930AM\"></sup>children and their wives into the lions’ den; and they had not reached the bottom of the den before the lions overpowered them and crushed all their bones.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Then Darius the king wrote to all the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21931AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21931AN\"></sup>peoples, nations and <i>men of every</i> language who were living in all the land: “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21931AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21931AO\"></sup>May your peace abound!",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>I <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21932AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21932AP\"></sup>make a decree that in all the dominion of my kingdom men are to fear and tremble before the God of Daniel;For He is the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21932AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21932AQ\"></sup>living God and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21932AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21932AR\"></sup>enduring forever,And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21932AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21932AS\"></sup>His kingdom is one which will not be destroyed,And His dominion <i>will be</i> forever.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>“He delivers and rescues and performs <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21933AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21933AT\"></sup>signs and wondersIn heaven and on earth,Who has <i>also</i> delivered Daniel from the power of the lions.”",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>So this <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21934AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21934AU\"></sup>Daniel enjoyed success in the reign of Darius and in the reign of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21934AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21934AV\"></sup>Cyrus the Persian."
		},
		"7": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">7 </span>In the first year of Belshazzar king of Babylon Daniel saw a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21935A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21935A\"></sup>dream and visions in his mind <i>as he lay</i> on his bed; then he <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21935B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21935B\"></sup>wrote the dream down <i>and</i> related the <i>following</i> summary of it.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Daniel said, “I was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21936C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21936C\"></sup>looking in my vision by night, and behold, the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21936D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21936D\"></sup>four winds of heaven were stirring up the great sea.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>And four great <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21937E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21937E\"></sup>beasts were coming up from the sea, different from one another.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>The first <i>was</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21938F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21938F\"></sup>like a lion and had <i>the</i> wings of an eagle. I kept looking until its wings were plucked, and it was lifted up from the ground and made to stand on two feet like a man; a human mind also was given to it.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>And behold, another beast, a second one, resembling a bear. And it was raised up on one side, and three ribs <i>were</i> in its mouth between its teeth; and thus they said to it, ‘Arise, devour much meat!’",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>After this I kept looking, and behold, another one, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21940G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21940G\"></sup>like a leopard, which had on its back four wings of a bird; the beast also had <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21940H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21940H\"></sup>four heads, and dominion was given to it.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>After this I kept looking in the night visions, and behold, a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21941I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21941I\"></sup>fourth beast, dreadful and terrifying and extremely strong; and it had large iron teeth. It devoured and crushed and trampled down the remainder with its feet; and it was different from all the beasts that were before it, and it had <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21941J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21941J\"></sup>ten horns.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>While I was contemplating the horns, behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21942K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21942K\"></sup>another horn, a little one, came up among them, and three of the first horns were pulled out by the roots before it; and behold, this horn possessed eyes like the eyes of a man and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21942L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21942L\"></sup>a mouth uttering great <i>boasts</i>.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>“I kept lookingUntil <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21943M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21943M\"></sup>thrones were set up,And the Ancient of Days took <i>His</i> seat;His <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21943N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21943N\"></sup>vesture <i>was</i> like white snowAnd the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21943O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21943O\"></sup>hair of His head like pure wool.His <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21943P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21943P\"></sup>throne <i>was</i> ablaze with flames,Its <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21943Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21943Q\"></sup>wheels <i>were</i> a burning fire.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>“A river of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21944R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21944R\"></sup>fire was flowingAnd coming out from before Him;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21944S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21944S\"></sup>Thousands upon thousands were attending Him,And myriads upon myriads were standing before Him;The <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21944T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21944T\"></sup>court sat,And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21944U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21944U\"></sup>the books were opened.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Then I kept looking because of the sound of the boastful words which the horn was speaking; I kept looking until the beast was slain, and its body was destroyed and given to the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21945V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21945V\"></sup>burning fire.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>As for the rest of the beasts, their dominion was taken away, but an extension of life was granted to them for an appointed period of time.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>“I kept looking in the night visions,And behold, with the clouds of heavenOne like a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21947W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21947W\"></sup>Son of Man was coming,And He came up to the Ancient of DaysAnd was presented before Him.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>“And to Him was given <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21948X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21948X\"></sup>dominion,Glory and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21948Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21948Y\"></sup>a kingdom,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21948Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21948Z\"></sup>That all the peoples, nations and <i>men of every</i> languageMight serve Him.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21948AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21948AA\"></sup>His dominion is an everlasting dominionWhich will not pass away;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21948AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21948AB\"></sup>And His kingdom is oneWhich will not be destroyed.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>“As for me, Daniel, my spirit was distressed within me, and the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21949AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21949AC\"></sup>visions in my mind kept <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21949AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21949AD\"></sup>alarming me.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>I approached one of those who were <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21950AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21950AE\"></sup>standing by and began asking him the exact meaning of all this. So he <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21950AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21950AF\"></sup>told me and made known to me the interpretation of these things:",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>‘These great beasts, which are four <i>in number</i>, are four kings <i>who</i> will arise from the earth.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>But the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21952AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21952AG\"></sup>saints of the Highest One will <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21952AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21952AH\"></sup>receive the kingdom and possess the kingdom forever, for all ages to come.’",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>“Then I desired to know the exact meaning of the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21953AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21953AI\"></sup>fourth beast, which was different from all the others, exceedingly dreadful, with its teeth of iron and its claws of bronze, <i>and which</i> devoured, crushed and trampled down the remainder with its feet,",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>and <i>the meaning</i> of the ten horns that <i>were</i> on its head and the other <i>horn</i> which came up, and before which three <i>of them</i> fell, namely, that horn which had eyes and a mouth uttering great <i>boasts</i> and which was larger in appearance than its associates.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>I kept looking, and that horn was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21955AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21955AJ\"></sup>waging war with the saints and overpowering them",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>until the Ancient of Days came and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21956AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21956AK\"></sup>judgment was passed in favor of the saints of the Highest One, and the time arrived when the saints took possession of the kingdom.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>“Thus he said: ‘The fourth beast will be a fourth kingdom on the earth, which will be different from all the <i>other</i> kingdoms and will devour the whole earth and tread it down and crush it.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>As for the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21958AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21958AL\"></sup>ten horns, out of this kingdom ten kings will arise; and another will arise after them, and he will be different from the previous ones and will subdue three kings.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>He will <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21959AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21959AM\"></sup>speak out against the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21959AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21959AN\"></sup>Most High and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21959AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21959AO\"></sup>wear down the saints of the Highest One, and he will intend to make <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21959AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21959AP\"></sup>alterations in times and in law; and they will be given into his hand for a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21959AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21959AQ\"></sup>time, times, and half a time.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>But the court will sit <i>for judgment</i>, and his dominion will be <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21960AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21960AR\"></sup>taken away, annihilated and destroyed forever.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Then the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21961AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21961AS\"></sup>sovereignty, the dominion and the greatness of <i>all</i> the kingdoms under the whole heaven will be given to the people of the saints of the Highest One; His kingdom <i>will be</i> an <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21961AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21961AT\"></sup>everlasting kingdom, and all the dominions will <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21961AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21961AU\"></sup>serve and obey Him.’",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>“At this point the revelation ended. As for me, Daniel, my thoughts were <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21962AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21962AV\"></sup>greatly alarming me and my face grew pale, but I <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21962AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21962AW\"></sup>kept the matter to myself.”"
		},
		"8": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">8 </span>In the third year of the reign of Belshazzar the king a vision appeared to me, Daniel, subsequent to the one which appeared to me previously.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>I <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21964A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21964A\"></sup>looked in the vision, and while I was looking I was in the citadel of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21964B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21964B\"></sup>Susa, which is in the province of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21964C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21964C\"></sup>Elam; and I looked in the vision and I myself was beside the Ulai Canal.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Then I lifted my eyes and looked, and behold, a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21965D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21965D\"></sup>ram which had two horns was standing in front of the canal. Now the two horns <i>were</i> long, but one <i>was</i> longer than the other, with the longer one coming up last.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>I saw the ram <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21966E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21966E\"></sup>butting westward, northward, and southward, and no <i>other</i> beasts could stand before him nor was there anyone to rescue from his power, but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21966F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21966F\"></sup>he did as he pleased and magnified <i>himself</i>.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>While I was observing, behold, a male goat was coming from the west over the surface of the whole earth without touching the ground; and the goat <i>had</i> a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21967G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21967G\"></sup>conspicuous horn between his eyes.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>He came up to the ram that had the two horns, which I had seen standing in front of the canal, and rushed at him in his mighty wrath.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>I saw him come beside the ram, and he was enraged at him; and he struck the ram and shattered his two horns, and the ram had no strength to withstand him. So he hurled him to the ground and trampled on him, and there was none to rescue the ram from his power.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Then the male goat magnified <i>himself</i> exceedingly. But as soon as <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21970H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21970H\"></sup>he was mighty, the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21970I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21970I\"></sup>large horn was broken; and in its place there came up four conspicuous <i>horns</i> toward the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21970J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21970J\"></sup>four winds of heaven.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Out of one of them came forth a rather <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21971K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21971K\"></sup>small horn which grew exceedingly great toward the south, toward the east, and toward the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21971L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21971L\"></sup>Beautiful <i>Land</i>.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>It grew up to the host of heaven and caused some of the host and some of the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21972M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21972M\"></sup>stars to fall to the earth, and it <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21972N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21972N\"></sup>trampled them down.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>It even <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21973O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21973O\"></sup>magnified <i>itself</i> to be equal with the Commander of the host; and it removed the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21973P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21973P\"></sup>regular sacrifice from Him, and the place of His sanctuary was thrown down.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And on account of transgression the host will be given over <i>to the horn</i> along with the regular sacrifice; and it will <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21974Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21974Q\"></sup>fling truth to the ground and perform <i>its will</i> and prosper.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Then I heard a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21975R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21975R\"></sup>holy one speaking, and another holy one said to that particular one who was speaking, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21975S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21975S\"></sup>How long will the vision <i>about</i> the regular sacrifice apply, while the transgression causes horror, so as to allow both the holy place and the host to be <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21975T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21975T\"></sup>trampled?”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>He said to me, “For <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21976U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21976U\"></sup>2,300 evenings <i>and</i> mornings; then the holy place will be properly restored.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>When <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21977V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21977V\"></sup>I, Daniel, had seen the vision, I sought to understand it; and behold, standing before me was one who looked like a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21977W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21977W\"></sup>man.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>And I heard the voice of a man between <i>the banks of</i> Ulai, and he called out and said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21978X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21978X\"></sup>Gabriel, give this <i>man</i> an understanding of the vision.”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>So he came near to where I was standing, and when he came I was frightened and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21979Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21979Y\"></sup>fell on my face; but he said to me, “Son of man, understand that the vision pertains to the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21979Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21979Z\"></sup>time of the end.”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Now while he was talking with me, I <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21980AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21980AA\"></sup>sank into a deep sleep with my face to the ground; but he <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21980AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21980AB\"></sup>touched me and made me stand upright.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>He said, “Behold, I am going to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21981AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21981AC\"></sup>let you know what will occur at the final period of the indignation, for <i>it</i> pertains to the appointed time of the end.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>The <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21982AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21982AD\"></sup>ram which you saw with the two horns represents the kings of Media and Persia.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>The shaggy goat <i>represents</i> the kingdom of Greece, and the large horn that is between his eyes is the first king.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>The <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21984AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21984AE\"></sup>broken <i>horn</i> and the four <i>horns that</i> arose in its place <i>represent</i> four kingdoms <i>which</i> will arise from <i>his</i> nation, although not with his power.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>“In the latter period of their rule,When the transgressors have run <i>their course</i>,A king will arise,Insolent and skilled in intrigue.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>“His power will be mighty, but not by his <i>own</i> power,And he will <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21986AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21986AF\"></sup>destroy to an extraordinary degreeAnd prosper and perform <i>his will</i>;He will destroy mighty men and the holy people.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>“And through his shrewdnessHe will cause deceit to succeed by his influence;And he will magnify <i>himself</i> in his heart,And he will destroy many while <i>they are</i> at ease.He will even <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21987AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21987AG\"></sup>oppose the Prince of princes,But he will be broken <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21987AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21987AH\"></sup>without human agency.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>“The vision of the evenings and morningsWhich has been told is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21988AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21988AI\"></sup>true;But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21988AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21988AJ\"></sup>keep the vision secret,For <i>it</i> pertains to many <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21988AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21988AK\"></sup>days <i>in the future</i>.”",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Then I, Daniel, was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21989AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21989AL\"></sup>exhausted and sick for days. Then I got up <i>again</i> and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21989AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21989AM\"></sup>carried on the king’s business; but I was astounded at the vision, and there was none to explain <i>it</i>."
		},
		"9": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">9 </span>In the first year of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21990A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21990A\"></sup>Darius the son of Ahasuerus, of Median descent, who was made king over the kingdom of the Chaldeans—",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>in the first year of his reign, I, Daniel, observed in the books the number of the years which was <i>revealed as</i> the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21991B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21991B\"></sup>Jeremiah the prophet for the completion of the desolations of Jerusalem, <i>namely</i>, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21991C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21991C\"></sup>seventy years.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>So I gave my attention to the Lord God to seek <i>Him by</i> prayer and supplications, with fasting, sackcloth and ashes.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>I prayed to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> my God and confessed and said, “Alas, O Lord, the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21993D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21993D\"></sup>great and awesome God, who <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21993E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21993E\"></sup>keeps His covenant and lovingkindness for those who love Him and keep His commandments,",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21994F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21994F\"></sup>we have sinned, committed iniquity, acted wickedly and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21994G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21994G\"></sup>rebelled, even <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21994H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21994H\"></sup>turning aside from Your commandments and ordinances.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Moreover, we have not <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21995I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21995I\"></sup>listened to Your servants the prophets, who spoke in Your name to our kings, our princes, our fathers and all the people of the land.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21996J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21996J\"></sup>Righteousness belongs to You, O Lord, but to us <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21996K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21996K\"></sup>open shame, as it is this day—to the men of Judah, the inhabitants of Jerusalem and all Israel, those who are nearby and those who are far away in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21996L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21996L\"></sup>all the countries to which You have driven them, because of their unfaithful deeds which they have committed against You.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Open shame belongs to us, O Lord, to our kings, our princes and our fathers, because we have sinned against You.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>To the Lord our God <i>belong</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21998M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21998M\"></sup>compassion and forgiveness, for we have <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21998N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21998N\"></sup>rebelled against Him;",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>nor have we obeyed the voice of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God, to walk in His teachings which He <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-21999O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-21999O\"></sup>set before us through His servants the prophets.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Indeed <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22000P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22000P\"></sup>all Israel has transgressed Your law and turned aside, not obeying Your voice; so the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22000Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22000Q\"></sup>curse has been poured out on us, along with the oath which is written in the law of Moses the servant of God, for we have sinned against Him.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Thus He has <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22001R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22001R\"></sup>confirmed His words which He had spoken against us and against our <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22001S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22001S\"></sup>rulers who ruled us, to bring on us great calamity; for under the whole heaven there has <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22001T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22001T\"></sup>not been done <i>anything</i> like what was done to Jerusalem.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>As it is written in the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22002U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22002U\"></sup>law of Moses, all this calamity has come on us; yet we have <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22002V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22002V\"></sup>not sought the favor of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God by <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22002W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22002W\"></sup>turning from our iniquity and giving attention to Your truth.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Therefore the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22003X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22003X\"></sup>kept the calamity in store and brought it on us; for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22003Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22003Y\"></sup>righteous with respect to all His deeds which He has done, but we have not obeyed His voice.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>“And now, O Lord our God, who have <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22004Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22004Z\"></sup>brought Your people out of the land of Egypt with a mighty hand and have <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22004AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22004AA\"></sup>made a name for Yourself, as it is this day—we have sinned, we have been wicked.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>O Lord, in accordance with all Your righteous acts, let now Your <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22005AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22005AB\"></sup>anger and Your wrath turn away from Your city Jerusalem, Your <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22005AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22005AC\"></sup>holy mountain; for because of our sins and the iniquities of our fathers, Jerusalem and Your people <i>have become</i> a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22005AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22005AD\"></sup>reproach to all those around us.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>So now, our God, listen to the prayer of Your servant and to his supplications, and for Your sake, O Lord, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22006AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22006AE\"></sup>let Your face shine on Your <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22006AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22006AF\"></sup>desolate sanctuary.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>O my God, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22007AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22007AG\"></sup>incline Your ear and hear! Open Your eyes and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22007AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22007AH\"></sup>see our desolations and the city which is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22007AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22007AI\"></sup>called by Your name; for we are not <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22007AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22007AJ\"></sup>presenting our supplications before You on account of any merits of our own, but on account of Your great compassion.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>O Lord, hear! O Lord, forgive! O Lord, listen and take action! For Your own sake, O my God, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22008AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22008AK\"></sup>do not delay, because Your city and Your people are called by Your name.”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Now while I was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22009AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22009AL\"></sup>speaking and praying, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22009AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22009AM\"></sup>confessing my sin and the sin of my people Israel, and presenting my supplication before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> my God in behalf of the holy mountain of my God,",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>while I was still speaking in prayer, then the man <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22010AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22010AN\"></sup>Gabriel, whom I had seen in the vision previously, came to me in <i>my</i> extreme weariness about the time of the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22010AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22010AO\"></sup>evening offering.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>He gave <i>me</i> instruction and talked with me and said, “O Daniel, I have now come forth to give you insight with <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22011AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22011AP\"></sup>understanding.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>At the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22012AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22012AQ\"></sup>beginning of your supplications the command was issued, and I have come to tell <i>you</i>, for you are <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22012AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22012AR\"></sup>highly esteemed; so give heed to the message and gain <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22012AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22012AS\"></sup>understanding of the vision.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>“Seventy <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22013AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22013AT\"></sup>weeks have been decreed for your people and your holy city, to finish the transgression, to make an end of sin, to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22013AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22013AU\"></sup>make atonement for iniquity, to bring in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22013AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22013AV\"></sup>everlasting righteousness, to seal up vision and prophecy and to anoint the most holy <i>place</i>.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>So you are to know and discern <i>that</i> from the issuing of a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22014AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22014AW\"></sup>decree to restore and rebuild Jerusalem until <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22014AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22014AX\"></sup>Messiah the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22014AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22014AY\"></sup>Prince <i>there will be</i> seven weeks and sixty-two weeks; it will be built again, with plaza and moat, even in times of distress.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Then after the sixty-two weeks the Messiah will be <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22015AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22015AZ\"></sup>cut off and have nothing, and the people of the prince who is to come will <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22015BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22015BA\"></sup>destroy the city and the sanctuary. And its end <i>will come</i> with a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22015BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22015BB\"></sup>flood; even to the end there will be war; desolations are determined.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>And he will make a firm covenant with the many for one week, but in the middle of the week he will put a stop to sacrifice and grain offering; and on the wing of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22016BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22016BC\"></sup>abominations <i>will come</i> one who makes desolate, even until a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22016BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22016BD\"></sup>complete destruction, one that is decreed, is poured out on the one who makes desolate.”"
		},
		"10": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">10 </span>In the third year of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22017A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22017A\"></sup>Cyrus king of Persia a message was revealed to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22017B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22017B\"></sup>Daniel, who was named Belteshazzar; and the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22017C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22017C\"></sup>message was true and <i>one of</i> great conflict, but he understood the message and had an <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22017D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22017D\"></sup>understanding of the vision.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>In those days, I, Daniel, had been <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22018E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22018E\"></sup>mourning for three entire weeks.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>I <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22019F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22019F\"></sup>did not eat any tasty food, nor did meat or wine enter my mouth, nor did I use any ointment at all until the entire three weeks were completed.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>On the twenty-fourth day of the first month, while I was by the bank of the great <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22020G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22020G\"></sup>river, that is, the Tigris,",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>I lifted my eyes and looked, and behold, there was a certain man <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22021H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22021H\"></sup>dressed in linen, whose waist was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22021I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22021I\"></sup>girded with <i>a belt of</i> pure <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22021J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22021J\"></sup>gold of Uphaz.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>His body also <i>was</i> like beryl, his face had the appearance of lightning, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22022K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22022K\"></sup>his eyes were like flaming torches, his arms and feet like the gleam of polished bronze, and the sound of his words like the sound of a tumult.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Now I, Daniel, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22023L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22023L\"></sup>alone saw the vision, while the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22023M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22023M\"></sup>men who were with me did not see the vision; nevertheless, a great <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22023N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22023N\"></sup>dread fell on them, and they ran away to hide themselves.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>So I was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22024O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22024O\"></sup>left alone and saw this great vision; yet <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22024P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22024P\"></sup>no strength was left in me, for my natural color turned to a deathly pallor, and I retained no strength.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>But I heard the sound of his words; and as soon as I heard the sound of his words, I <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22025Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22025Q\"></sup>fell into a deep sleep on my face, with my face to the ground.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Then behold, a hand <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22026R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22026R\"></sup>touched me and set me trembling on my hands and knees.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>He said to me, “O <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22027S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22027S\"></sup>Daniel, man of high esteem, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22027T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22027T\"></sup>understand the words that I am about to tell you and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22027U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22027U\"></sup>stand upright, for I have now been sent to you.” And when he had spoken this word to me, I stood up <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22027V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22027V\"></sup>trembling.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Then he said to me, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22028W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22028W\"></sup>Do not be afraid, Daniel, for from the first day that you set your heart on understanding <i>this</i> and on <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22028X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22028X\"></sup>humbling yourself before your God, your words were heard, and I have come in response <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22028Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22028Y\"></sup>to your words.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>But the prince of the kingdom of Persia was withstanding me for twenty-one days; then behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22029Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22029Z\"></sup>Michael, one of the chief princes, came to help me, for I had been left there with the kings of Persia.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Now I have come to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22030AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22030AA\"></sup>give you an understanding of what will happen to your people in the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22030AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22030AB\"></sup>latter days, for the vision pertains to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22030AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22030AC\"></sup>the days yet <i>future</i>.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>When he had spoken to me according to these words, I turned my face toward the ground and became <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22031AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22031AD\"></sup>speechless.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>And behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22032AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22032AE\"></sup>one who resembled a human being was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22032AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22032AF\"></sup>touching my lips; then I opened my mouth and spoke and said to him who was standing before me, “O my lord, as a result of the vision <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22032AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22032AG\"></sup>anguish has come upon me, and I have retained no strength.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>For <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22033AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22033AH\"></sup>how can such a servant of my lord talk with such as my lord? As for me, there remains just now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22033AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22033AI\"></sup>no strength in me, nor has any breath been left in me.”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Then <i>this</i> one with human appearance touched me again and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22034AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22034AJ\"></sup>strengthened me.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>He said, “O man of high esteem, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22035AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22035AK\"></sup>do not be afraid. Peace be with you; take <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22035AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22035AL\"></sup>courage and be courageous!” Now as soon as he spoke to me, I received strength and said, “May my lord speak, for you have <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22035AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22035AM\"></sup>strengthened me.”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Then he said, “Do you understand why I came to you? But I shall now return to fight against the prince of Persia; so I am going forth, and behold, the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22036AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22036AN\"></sup>prince of Greece is about to come.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>However, I will tell you what is inscribed in the writing of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22037AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22037AO\"></sup>truth. Yet there is no one who stands firmly with me against these <i>forces</i> except <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22037AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22037AP\"></sup>Michael your prince."
		},
		"11": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">11 </span>“In the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22038A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22038A\"></sup>first year of Darius the Mede, I arose to be an encouragement and a protection for him.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And now I will tell you the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22039B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22039B\"></sup>truth. Behold, three more kings are going to arise in Persia. Then a fourth will gain far more riches than all <i>of them</i>; as soon as he becomes strong through his riches, he will arouse the whole <i>empire</i> against the realm of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22039C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22039C\"></sup>Greece.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>And a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22040D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22040D\"></sup>mighty king will arise, and he will rule with great authority and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22040E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22040E\"></sup>do as he pleases.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>But as soon as he has arisen, his kingdom will be broken up and parceled out <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22041F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22041F\"></sup>toward the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22041G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22041G\"></sup>four points of the compass, though not to his <i>own</i> descendants, nor according to his authority which he wielded, for his sovereignty will be <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22041H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22041H\"></sup>uprooted and <i>given</i> to others besides them.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>“Then the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22042I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22042I\"></sup>king of the South will grow strong, along with <i>one</i> of his princes who will gain ascendancy over him and obtain dominion; his domain <i>will be</i> a great dominion <i>indeed</i>.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>After some years they will form an alliance, and the daughter of the king of the South will come to the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22043J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22043J\"></sup>king of the North to carry out a peaceful arrangement. But she will not retain her position of power, nor will he remain with his power, but she will be given up, along with those who brought her in and the one who sired her as well as he who supported her in <i>those</i> times.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>But one of the descendants of her line will arise in his place, and he will come against <i>their</i> army and enter the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22044K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22044K\"></sup>fortress of the king of the North, and he will deal with them and display <i>great</i> strength.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Also their <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22045L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22045L\"></sup>gods with their metal images <i>and</i> their precious vessels of silver and gold he will take into captivity to Egypt, and he on his part will refrain from <i>attacking</i> the king of the North for <i>some</i> years.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Then the latter will enter the realm of the king of the South, but will return to his <i>own</i> land.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>“His sons will mobilize and assemble a multitude of great forces; and one of them will keep on coming and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22047M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22047M\"></sup>overflow and pass through, that he may again wage war up to his <i>very</i> fortress.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>The <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22048N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22048N\"></sup>king of the South will be enraged and go forth and fight with the king of the North. Then the latter will raise a great multitude, but <i>that</i> multitude will be given into the hand of the <i>former</i>.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>When the multitude is carried away, his heart will be lifted up, and he will cause tens of thousands to fall; yet he will not prevail.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>For the king of the North will again raise a greater multitude than the former, and after an <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22050O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22050O\"></sup>interval of some years he will press on with a great army and much equipment.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>“Now in those times many will rise up against the king of the South; the violent ones among your people will also lift themselves up in order to fulfill the vision, but they will fall down.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Then the king of the North will come, cast up a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22052P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22052P\"></sup>siege ramp and capture a well-fortified city; and the forces of the South will not stand <i>their ground</i>, not even their choicest troops, for there will be no strength to make a stand.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>But he who comes against him will <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22053Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22053Q\"></sup>do as he pleases, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22053R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22053R\"></sup>no one will <i>be able to</i> withstand him; he will also stay <i>for a time</i> in the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22053S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22053S\"></sup>Beautiful Land, with destruction in his hand.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>He will <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22054T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22054T\"></sup>set his face to come with the power of his whole kingdom, bringing with him a proposal of peace which he will put into effect; he will also give him the daughter of women to ruin it. But she will not take a stand <i>for him</i> or be on his side.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Then he will turn his face to the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22055U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22055U\"></sup>coastlands and capture many. But a commander will put a stop to his scorn against him; moreover, he will <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22055V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22055V\"></sup>repay him for his scorn.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>So he will turn his face toward the fortresses of his own land, but he will <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22056W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22056W\"></sup>stumble and fall and be <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22056X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22056X\"></sup>found no more.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>“Then in his place one will arise who will <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22057Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22057Y\"></sup>send an oppressor through the Jewel of <i>his</i> kingdom; yet within a few days he will be shattered, though not in anger nor in battle.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>In his place a despicable person will arise, on whom the honor of kingship has not been conferred, but he will come in a time of tranquility and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22058Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22058Z\"></sup>seize the kingdom by intrigue.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>The overflowing <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22059AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22059AA\"></sup>forces will be flooded away before him and shattered, and also the prince of the covenant.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>After an alliance is made with him he will practice deception, and he will go up and gain power with a small <i>force of</i> people.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>In a time of tranquility he will enter the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22061AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22061AB\"></sup>richest <i>parts</i> of the realm, and he will accomplish what his fathers never did, nor his ancestors; he will distribute plunder, booty and possessions among them, and he will devise his schemes against strongholds, but <i>only</i> for a time.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>He will stir up his strength and courage against the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22062AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22062AC\"></sup>king of the South with a large army; so the king of the South will mobilize an extremely large and mighty army for war; but he will not stand, for schemes will be devised against him.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Those who eat his choice food will destroy him, and his army will <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22063AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22063AD\"></sup>overflow, but many will fall down slain.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>As for both kings, their hearts will be <i>intent</i> on <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22064AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22064AE\"></sup>evil, and they will <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22064AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22064AF\"></sup>speak lies <i>to each other</i> at the same table; but it will not succeed, for the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22064AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22064AG\"></sup>end is still <i>to come</i> at the appointed time.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Then he will return to his land with much plunder; but his heart will be <i>set</i> against the holy covenant, and he will take action and <i>then</i> return to his <i>own</i> land.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>“At the appointed time he will return and come into the South, but this last time it will not turn out the way it did before.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>For ships of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22067AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22067AH\"></sup>Kittim will come against him; therefore he will be disheartened and will return and become enraged at the holy covenant and take action; so he will come back and show regard for those who forsake the holy covenant.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Forces from him will arise, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22068AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22068AI\"></sup>desecrate the sanctuary fortress, and do away with the regular sacrifice. And they will set up the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22068AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22068AJ\"></sup>abomination of desolation.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>By <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22069AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22069AK\"></sup>smooth <i>words</i> he will turn to godlessness those who act wickedly toward the covenant, but the people who know their God will display <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22069AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22069AL\"></sup>strength and take action.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22070AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22070AM\"></sup>Those who have insight among the people will give understanding to the many; yet they will <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22070AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22070AN\"></sup>fall by sword and by flame, by captivity and by plunder for <i>many</i> days.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>Now when they fall they will be granted a little help, and many will <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22071AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22071AO\"></sup>join with them in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22071AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22071AP\"></sup>hypocrisy.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>Some of those who have insight will fall, in order to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22072AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22072AQ\"></sup>refine, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22072AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22072AR\"></sup>purge and make them <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22072AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22072AS\"></sup>pure until the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22072AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22072AT\"></sup>end time; because <i>it is</i> still <i>to come</i> at the appointed time.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>“Then the king will <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22073AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22073AU\"></sup>do as he pleases, and he will exalt and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22073AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22073AV\"></sup>magnify himself above every god and will <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22073AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22073AW\"></sup>speak monstrous things against the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22073AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22073AX\"></sup>God of gods; and he will prosper until the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22073AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22073AY\"></sup>indignation is finished, for that which is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22073AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22073AZ\"></sup>decreed will be done.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>He will show no regard for the gods of his fathers or for the desire of women, nor will he show regard for any <i>other</i> god; for he will magnify himself above <i>them</i> all.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>But instead he will honor a god of fortresses, a god whom his fathers did not know; he will honor <i>him</i> with gold, silver, costly stones and treasures.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>He will take action against the strongest of fortresses with <i>the help of</i> a foreign god; he will give great honor to those who acknowledge <i>him</i> and will cause them to rule over the many, and will parcel out land for a price.",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>“At the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22077BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22077BA\"></sup>end time the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22077BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22077BB\"></sup>king of the South will collide with him, and the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22077BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22077BC\"></sup>king of the North will <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22077BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22077BD\"></sup>storm against him with chariots, with horsemen and with many ships; and he will enter countries, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22077BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22077BE\"></sup>overflow <i>them</i> and pass through.",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>He will also enter the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22078BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22078BF\"></sup>Beautiful Land, and many <i>countries</i> will fall; but these will be rescued out of his hand: Edom, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22078BG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BG&quot;&gt;BG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22078BG\"></sup>Moab and the foremost of the sons of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22078BH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BH&quot;&gt;BH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22078BH\"></sup>Ammon.",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>Then he will stretch out his hand against <i>other</i> countries, and the land of Egypt will not escape.",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>But he will gain control over the hidden treasures of gold and silver and over all the precious things of Egypt; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22080BI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BI&quot;&gt;BI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22080BI\"></sup>Libyans and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22080BJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BJ&quot;&gt;BJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22080BJ\"></sup>Ethiopians <i>will follow</i> at his heels.",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>But rumors from the East and from the North will disturb him, and he will go forth with great wrath to destroy and annihilate many.",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>He will pitch the tents of his royal pavilion between the seas and the beautiful <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22082BK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BK&quot;&gt;BK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22082BK\"></sup>Holy Mountain; yet he will come to his end, and no one will help him."
		},
		"12": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">12 </span>“Now at that time <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22083A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22083A\"></sup>Michael, the great prince who stands <i>guard</i> over the sons of your people, will arise. And there will be a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22083B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22083B\"></sup>time of distress <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22083C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22083C\"></sup>such as never occurred since there was a nation until that time; and at that time your people, everyone who is found written in the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22083D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22083D\"></sup>book, will be rescued.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22084E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22084E\"></sup>Many of those who sleep in the dust of the ground will awake, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22084F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22084F\"></sup>these to everlasting life, but the others to disgrace <i>and</i> everlasting contempt.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Those who have <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22085G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22085G\"></sup>insight will <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22085H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22085H\"></sup>shine brightly like the brightness of the expanse of heaven, and those who <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22085I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22085I\"></sup>lead the many to righteousness, like the stars forever and ever.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>But as for you, Daniel, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22086J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22086J\"></sup>conceal these words and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22086K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22086K\"></sup>seal up the book until the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22086L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22086L\"></sup>end of time; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22086M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22086M\"></sup>many will go back and forth, and knowledge will increase.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Then I, Daniel, looked and behold, two others were standing, one on this bank of the river and the other on that bank of the river.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22088N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22088N\"></sup>one said to the man <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22088O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22088O\"></sup>dressed in linen, who was above the waters of the river, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22088P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22088P\"></sup>How long <i>will it be</i> until the end of <i>these</i> wonders?”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>I heard the man dressed in linen, who was above the waters of the river, as he <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22089Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22089Q\"></sup>raised his right hand and his left toward heaven, and swore by <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22089R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22089R\"></sup>Him who lives forever that it would be for a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22089S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22089S\"></sup>time, times, and half <i>a</i> <i>time</i>; and as soon as they finish <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22089T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22089T\"></sup>shattering the power of the holy people, all these <i>events</i> will be completed.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>As for me, I heard but could not understand; so I said, “My lord, what <i>will be</i> the outcome of these <i>events</i>?”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>He said, “Go <i>your way</i>, Daniel, for <i>these</i> words are concealed and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22091U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22091U\"></sup>sealed up until the end time.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22092V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22092V\"></sup>Many will be purged, purified and refined, but the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22092W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22092W\"></sup>wicked will act wickedly; and none of the wicked will understand, but those who <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22092X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22092X\"></sup>have insight will understand.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>From the time that the regular sacrifice is abolished and the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22093Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22093Y\"></sup>abomination of desolation is set up, <i>there will be</i> 1,290 days.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>How <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22094Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22094Z\"></sup>blessed is he who keeps waiting and attains to the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22094AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22094AA\"></sup>1,335 days!",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>But as for you, go <i>your way</i> to the end; then you will enter into <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22095AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22095AB\"></sup>rest and rise <i>again</i> for your <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-22095AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-22095AC\"></sup>allotted portion at the end of the age.”"
		}
	}
};
module.exports = book;